snippet.textDisplay:
We have exactly same named tax in Turkey. Either it's different in UK or you got that wrong. VAT is the weirdest tax kind i have ever seen. In Turkey, it's like this; let's say you made 10k this month.

10.000/118=84,75x100=8.475
10.000-8.475=1.525 This is your VAT.

It's not a guess or something they assume.
It's based on your income before any expenses.

Now if you want that money back you need to present expenses to the government. There is a list. If you buy groceries you get %8 VAT back. If you buy electronics its %18. So on.

Let's say you bought a 2k laptop. That's 306 VAT back. So it's impossible to get them all back unless you know what. These bad tax systems forcing people to cheat. Even if you lose money you still have to pay VAT. Maybe it's different in UK but it's exactly the same name.

(Value-added tax - Katma Değer Vergisi)

snippet.textDisplay:
Printer tech here:

I know how annoying it is to want to print something black and white but the printer won’t let you because it needs colored ink/toner. You can fix this issue by going into the printer properties when you go to print on your computer/laptop and change one of the printer settings to “Grayscale”. Grayscale allows you to print black and white without the need of colored ink/toner. NOTE: This does not work for all printers. Some printers will not let you bypass the error of “you need colored ink.” Some printers need all the colors and won’t print black because of clumping issues. And believe it or not, even if your printing a black and white picture, some printers still use color ink/toner with the black to print a black and white page to make it more vibrant and clean.
